{"_id":"8mrj2yneMVyqrcdP","name":"Dynamic Backlash","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{},"description":"A Critical Failure on an arcane skill check results in Fatigue (described on page 151). If you feel magic should come with a higher price, however, use this table instead.","results":[{"_id":"d7lytHKHdu9TW9E4","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Catastrophe: Something goes terribly wrong. The GM must decide what, but some ideas are a new and permanent Minor Hindrance, the inability to use powers for several days, or an explosion of some sort. The backlash should be thematic if possible. If the hero tampers with dark forces for his abilities, for example, he might become corrupted or summon something sinister into the world. If he’s a weird scientist the device might explode for 3d6 damage in a Medium Blast Template, or he might develop a Quirk, Phobia, or other “madness.”","img":"icons/svg/biohazard.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"qlDbVNjMbvuVDT2Q","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Backfire: The power succeeds as with a raise but affects a different target with the worst possible results. A bolt hits a random friend, boost Trait increases an enemy’s skill or attribute, etc. If there’s no likely target, he’s Stunned instead. If the power has a Duration other than Instant, it lasts its full term and can only be negated by dispel (the caster can’t voluntarily end it herself).","img":"icons/svg/lightning.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"2ciLzSOEL6EcvxOL","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Short Circuit: The power fails but the Power Points allocated to it are spent, along with an additional 1d6 Power Points.","img":"icons/svg/ice-aura.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"Y7QxaJw2ajgtzyv9","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Stunned: The caster is Stunned (see page 106). She subtracts 2 from arcane skill rolls for the rest of the encounter (the penalty remains –2 even if she gets this result again).","img":"icons/svg/explosion.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,8],"drawn":false},{"_id":"xBv3MRRULrsvafBL","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Overload: The character’s synapses crackle and overload with power. He takes 2d6 damage plus the cost of the power in Power Points, including any Power Modifiers the player declared.","img":"icons/svg/stoned.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[9,10],"drawn":false},{"_id":"rU52DETuRuxbW2zq","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Fatigue: The character suffers Fatigue.","img":"icons/svg/falling.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[11,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"Biij1nanL7hmvU2L","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Overcharge: The power draws ambient energy from the air, automatically succeeding against the target with a raise and costing the caster no Power Points!","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[12,12],"drawn":false}],"formula":"2d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"DG6OZSwe8iyosQw2","name":"Fear Table","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{},"description":"","results":[{"_id":"bOEyTDng76vfghJO","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Adrenaline Surge: The hero’s “fight” response takes over. He acts as if he had a Joker this action!","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"RLn5A0GiEoZ9XuL1","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Distracted: The hero is Distracted until the end of his next turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,6],"drawn":false},{"_id":"9rJtASIMlJ8PuOON","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Vulnerable: The target is Vulnerable until the end of his next turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[7,9],"drawn":false},{"_id":"kpOtG2dq3nUeHEgY","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Shaken: The character is Shaken.","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[10,12],"drawn":false},{"_id":"if4L0vegL9gjrwEl","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The Mark of Fear: The hero is Stunned and suffers some cosmetic physical alteration—a white streak forms in his hair, his eyes twitch constantly, or some other minor physical alteration manifests.","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[13,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"7EWM7q1QCdCjZ358","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Frightened: The character gains the Hesitant Hindrance for the remainder of the encounter. If he already has it, he’s Panicked instead.","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[14,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"x0Dj2xP1UDZcY4L6","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Panicked: The character immediately moves his full Pace plus running die away from the danger and is Shaken.","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[16,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"WvfZgSuGvwLdT93m","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Minor Phobia: The character gains a Minor Phobia Hindrance somehow associated with the trauma.","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"0YLIqUuYJt2dX8Ba","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Major Phobia: The character gains the Major Phobia Hindrance.","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[20,21],"drawn":false},{"_id":"s9C8hnIwEgBcb74k","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Heart Attack: The hero is so overwhelmed with fear that his heart stutters. He must make an immediate Vigor roll at –2. If successful, he’s Stunned. If he fails, he’s Incapacitated and dies in 2d6 rounds. In the latter case, a Healing roll at –4 saves his life, but he remains Incapacitated. He may be treated normally thereafter.","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[22,30],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"Mwe47I6tfWtwDdsM","name":"Vehicle Out of Control","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{},"description":"Damage caused by an Out of Control roll doesn’t trigger another Out of Control roll, but a Wound triggers a Critical Hit as usual.","results":[{"_id":"E4f6cEapDjGXaOG5","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Major Collision: Everyone in the vehicle is Distracted. It takes d4 Wounds and one Critical Hit.","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"YH9RU1yWwF2VGTBY","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Minor Collision: The vehicle takes a Wound and a Critical Hit.","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"GufNlib5pctdT97t","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Distracted: Ground vehicles spin out or skid. Airplanes or spaceships stall, slide, flip, or roll unexpectedly. Everyone on board is Distracted until the end of their next turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,9],"drawn":false},{"_id":"YaqvLD2XJsCyve1P","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Vulnerable: The vehicle and everyone on board is Vulnerable until the end of their next turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[10,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"9BtTQ3ktyAppjUt7","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Glitch: Something is jarred loose or breaks from rough handling. The vehicle suffers a Critical Hit (reroll Crew results).","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[12,12],"drawn":false}],"formula":"2d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"MxN4Gq9QmhDkkuTv","name":"Creative Combat","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"gm-notes":{}},"description":"A successful Test (page 108) works as usual, but if a Wild Card character succeeds\r\nwith a raise while in combat, her foe is not automatically Shaken — she rolls on the Creative Combat table instead:","results":[{"_id":"kgKcT6QdfEbB5zwz","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Second Wind: The foe’s reaction gives your hero hope or allows her to catch her breath. She may remove a level of Fatigue or a Wound (her choice). If she doesn’t have Fatigue or Wounds, the enemy is Shaken instead.","img":"icons/svg/regen.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"A94ht2yHzyeQrP0G","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Inspiration: Fate favors the bold. The clever hero receives a Benny.","img":"icons/svg/coins.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ifpOnbJSPOJ38Sa9","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Double Whammy: The target is both Distracted and Vulnerable.","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"yDQIGUkDhVwcTV2T","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Shaken: The foe is Shaken.","img":"icons/svg/ice-aura.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,8],"drawn":false},{"_id":"AeNcijQvvLtv0o9t","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Setback: The target suffers a setback of some sort. She might fall off a ledge, lose the confidence of her minions (who then desert her), take a rash but foolish action, or simply lose her next action as she attempts to recover from whatever situation she finds herself in.","img":"icons/svg/falling.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[9,10],"drawn":false},{"_id":"2aM9RtFglW9Qm1b0","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Insight: The hero has new insight into the target’s nature. Once during this encounter, she may add +d6 to any Trait roll made to directly attack, affect, or damage the same foe. If rolled a second time in the same encounter, the foe is Shaken instead.","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[11,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"goTpN3DyWRvUvSRr","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Seize the Moment: After the hero resolves this turn, she immediately gets an entire additional turn. This includes movement as well! She may use the turn to go on Hold if she wishes.","img":"icons/svg/angel.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[12,12],"drawn":false}],"formula":"2d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
