{"_id":"qLvoTXBMQemOcbkp","name":"Vehicle Critical Hits","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{},"description":"","results":[{"_id":"5W8qIDhRXBMbgJxN","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Scratch and Dent: The attack just scratches the paint or passes clean through the body without hitting anyone or anything vital. There’s no permanent damage.","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"tB6cUOJMSicYef2R","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Guidance/Traction: The wheels, tracks, sails, thrusters, etc. have been hit. Reduce Handling by one each time this occurs (to a maximum penalty of –4).","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"IRQjbMNYb5OdoN4X","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Locomotion: The engine, mainsails, boiler, etc., is hit. Top Speed is reduced by 10% each time this occurs (to a minimum of 60% Top Speed).","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"U11UddJzdpETEGfi","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Chassis: The vehicle suffers a hit in the body with no special effects.","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,8],"drawn":false},{"_id":"6evQ1JEWz8zugcZC","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Crew: For direct damage, subtract the vehicle’s Armor (if appropriate for the victim’s position) and apply the remainder to a random crew member. Area effect weapons affect everyone in a section determined by the GM. If this is the result of a Collision, the occupants are Shaken.","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[9,10],"drawn":false},{"_id":"gnK3wihUGLOSceTd","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Weapon: A random weapon is destroyed. If there is no weapon, this is a Chassis hit instead.","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[11,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ANHqtkjUSPDZKCh4","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"System: The vehicle loses an electronic system, its airbags, or some other system determined by the GM. If it doesn’t have any special features, treat this as a Chassis hit instead.","img":"icons/svg/d20-highlight.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[12,12],"drawn":false}],"formula":"2d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
